"title": "5834: disagreement",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5834",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A failure to be of one mind, which should be avoided whenever possible within the church, the family and other areas of everyday life. Christians are urged to maintain the unity of the church and avoid damaging division.</p>\n<h2>Disagreement within the church</h2>\n<h3>Between individuals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:2\">PHP 4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:33-Mark9:34\">MRK 9:33–9:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:46\">LUK 9:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:36-Acts15:40\">ACT 15:36–15:40</a> <em>these differences later reconciled; see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:6\">1Co 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:11\">2Ti 4:11</a></em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:11-1Cor1:12\">1CO 1:11–1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:3-1Cor3:4\">1CO 3:3–3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:20\">2CO 12:20</a></p>\n<h3>About doctrine</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:1-Acts15:2\">ACT 15:1–15:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:11-Acts15:14\">ACT 15:11–15:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:19-Acts15:20\">ACT 15:19–15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:11-Gal2:14\">GAL 2:11–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Disagreement in the family</h2>\n<h3>May cause estrangement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:6\">MIC 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:41-Gen27:45\">GEN 27:41–27:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:4\">GEN 37:4</a></p>\n<h3>Is unpleasant to live with</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:13\">PRO 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:9\">PRO 21:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:19\">PRO 21:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:24\">PRO 25:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:15\">PRO 27:15</a></p>\n<h2>Disagreement among witnesses</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:56\">MRK 14:56</a></strong> <em>The background to this statement is <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:15\">Dt 19:15</a>, which demands that conviction can only take place on the testimony of two or three agreed witnesses.</em></p>\n<h2>The wisdom of avoiding disagreement</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:14\">2TI 2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:14\">PRO 17:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:3\">PRO 20:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:17\">PRO 26:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:21\">PRO 26:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:17\">ROM 16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:23\">2TI 2:23</a></p>\n<h3>To prevent division</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:25\">MAT 12:25</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:24-Mark3:25\">MRK 3:24–3:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:17\">LUK 11:17</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:16-1Kgs12:17\">1KI 12:16–12:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:16-2Chr10:17\">2CH 10:16–10:17</a></p>\n<h2>Sin provokes disagreement</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:19-Gal5:20\">GAL 5:19–5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:12-Prov6:14\">PRO 6:12–6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:19\">PRO 17:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:9-Titus3:11\">TIT 3:9–3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:16\">JAS 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>Examples where disagreement is inevitable</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:1-1Sam11:2\">1SA 11:1–11:2</a> <em>Nahash's suggestion to the men of Jabesh Gilead</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:8\">1KI 20:8</a> <em>Ben-Hadad's demands on Ahab</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of resolved disagreement</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:5-Gen13:9\">GEN 13:5–13:9</a> <em>Abraham and Lot resolve their disagreement over land and livestock</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:19-Gen26:22\">GEN 26:19–26:22</a> <em>Isaac settles a disagreement about the water supply</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:16-1Kgs3:27\">1KI 3:16–3:27</a> <em>Solomon resolves a disagreement between two prostitutes.</em></p>\n<h2>Ways to resolve disagreement</h2>\n<h3>Settlement out of court</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:25\">MAT 5:25</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:58\">LUK 12:58</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:1\">1CO 6:1</a></p>\n<h3>Accepting weaknesses</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1\">ROM 14:1</a></p>\n<h3>Striving for harmony</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:10\">1CO 1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:19\">ROM 14:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:5\">ROM 15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:11\">2CO 13:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:3\">EPH 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:2-Phil2:3\">PHP 2:2–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:13-Col3:15\">COL 3:13–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:13\">1TH 5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:23-2Tim2:24\">2TI 2:23–2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:8\">1PE 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Appointing wise leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:12-Deut1:13\">DEU 1:12–1:13</a></strong> <em>Moses realised that he was unable to deal with all the people's disputes alone.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15-Matt18:17\">MAT 18:15–18:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:5-1Cor6:6\">1CO 6:5–6:6</a></p>\n<h3>Being of sound doctrine</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:3-1Tim1:4\">1TI 1:3–1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:9-Titus3:10\">TIT 3:9–3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Those who seek to resolve disagreement are blessed</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:9\">MAT 5:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:18\">JAS 3:18</a></p>",
